<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="seat-n">seat <strong><em>n</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /siːt/    美 /siːt/  </p>
<p>[C]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>座；座位：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Seats must be booked in advance. 
必须提前订座。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>席位：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>A promotion for him would mean a seat on the board of directors. 
他升职意味着将在董事会拥有一个席位。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>中心；所在地；宅邸：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a family / country seat 
私家/乡间宅邸</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She moved her family into the county seat. 
她把全家搬到了县城里。</p><footer>2010 江苏改</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="have-take-a-seat">have / take a seat</h3>
<p>1.<strong>坐下：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Take a seat, please. 
请坐。</p></div>

<h3 id="take-ones-seat">take one’s seat</h3>
<p>1.<strong>就座：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>They took their seats at the small round table. 
他们在小圆桌旁就座。</p></div></div>